60167.desc:
1. Multiple random Bosses appear every Thursday, with one unlocked daily at 05:00.
2. Complete the current Difficulty to unlock the next. Challenge progress and rewards reset every Thursday.
3. A successful challenge locks the used Modifier, which can no longer be used on other Bosses. Locked modifiers reset every Thursday.
4. Failed challenges do not lock Modifiers.
5. Before collecting rewards, the Admin can reset the progress of previously challenged Bosses. Stage objectives for those Boss stages will be cleared and Modifier locks removed.
6. Once the Regular Dream Outphase Level has opened, if rewards have not been collected, the Admin can reset the Dream Difficulty, but all progress at the current Difficulty will be cleared.

60189.desc:

2. Hazard Zones: Core have 3 goals and rewards differ by number of goals completed.
3. Stage content and rewards refresh every Monday and Thursday.
4. Completing Hazard Zone: Periphery provides positive Indicias, with 1 Indicia unlocked per completed zone.
5. System Indicia are effective for all stages, with blue Indicia applying to Modifiers and red Indicia to enemies.
6. When the Hazard Zone: Core is complete, the next refresh will unlock the following difficulty level.
7. Before claiming the rewards, the difficulty level may be changed. Once the difficulty level is changed, the Hazard Zone stage progress will be reset.

60190.desc:

2. Completion rewards for each stage can only be claimed once.
3. Areas open up as you level up, with increasing difficulty level and numbers of Indicia.
4. The 5th stage in every area is an Elite Stage, the 10th a Boss Stage.

71164.desc:
Sigils:
1. Equip Sigils to give your Modifier buffs and Combat Power.
2. Each Sigil offers two main buffs that are enhanced with leveling up, as well as several Indicia (which do not enhance with leveling up) and several Enchant slots for Enchant Skills.
3. The buffs granted depend on the Sigil in question. The higher the Sigil's grade, the better the buff.
4. Select the most appropriate Sigil for your character for maximum benefits.

Sigil Positions:
1. Sigils must be equipped at the corresponding Sigil Positions.

Sigil Sets:
1. Set effects, which grant additional buff bonuses or effects, are triggered when three or more Sigils of the same Set are equipped.

71165.desc:
Enhance/LimitBreak:
1. Enhance your Sigil to level it up.
2. The higher the Sigil level, the better the main buffs granted by the Sigil.
3. To enhance the Sigil to Lv. 10, Lv. 20, Lv. 30, Lv. 40, and Lv. 50, the use of LimitBreak materials is first needed to break the level cap.
4. Character-exclusive skill slots may be unlocked when the Sigil is enhanced to Lv. 50 and Lv. 60.

Reconstruct:
1. Use Reconstructors to reconstruct Sigils. Reconstruction also provides additional Gen-zone exclusive buffs.
2. Clarifying Reconstruction can be carried out on Sigils that have been reconstructed to give the corresponding Modifier even more exclusive buffs.

Enchant:
1. One Enchant Slot is unlocked when the Sigil is enhanced to Lv. 30 and Lv. 40 respectively. Each Enchant slot can house up to 2 Enchant skills.
2. Use Enchant materials and Ain Soph Coins to carry out Sigil Enchants. Enchant skills provide the Modifier with additional buffs.

Warp:
1. 5-Star Sigils may be enhanced to Lv. 60 after its Modifier-exclusive Reconstruction has been activated. Enhancing the Sigil to Lv. 50 and Lv. 60 will also unlock an equipable Modifier-exclusive skill slot each time.
2. Use the corresponding materials to unlock the slot skills of your choice.

Forge:
Admins may also choose to forge an existing Sigil into another of their choice. The new Sigil will however retain its original Grade, Position, Level, Enchant skills, Clarifying Reconstruction effects, and Warp Skills. Forge costs vary between Sigils.

420121.desc:
1. In Whispers in the Woods, stages are classified as Rustling, Whispering and Germinating.
2. Clear Rustling and Whispering stages to gain Pinecones and use them to purchase items in Shimogyou Groceries.
3. Rustling stages cost Swigs.
4. Whispering stages cost Hunting Permits, which can be obtained by completing event missions or by purchasing at Shimogyou Groceries.
5. In Whispering, Bawling stages are harder than Wailing stages, but they also drop more Pinecones.
6. In Whispering, you can complete Bawling stages within a specified time to unlock Beast Tide stages in Germinating.
7. Beast Tide stages will be scored based on how long it takes you to clear them. Upon completion, your highest score will be recorded and a ranking will be given.

420122.desc:
1. In Towards the Flames, stages are classified as Survival Instinct, Total Determination and Wildfire Burning.
2. Clear Survival Instinct and Total Determination stages to gain Candy Apples and use them to purchase items in Shimogyou Market.
3. Survival Instinct stages cost Swigs.
4. Total Determination stages cost Fire Bows, which can be obtained by completing event missions or by purchasing at Shimogyou Market.
5. In Total Determination, Great Fury stages are harder than Evil Spirit stages, but they also drop more Candy Apples.
6. In Total Determination, you can complete Great Fury stages within a specified time to unlock To the Flames stages in Wildfire Burning.
7. To the Flames stages will be scored based on how long it takes you to clear them. Upon completion, your highest score will be recorded and a ranking will be given.

420123.desc:
1. In this mode, points are scored by killing oncoming enemies. Stage rewards are based on the highest score achieved by the end.
2. Each stage grants Modifiers a certain basic buff. Defeat a certain number of enemies to get an enhancement effect. Every time an enhancement effect is gained, the next enhancement effect comes with an additional buff. This process continues until all the buffs are obtained.
3. Each stage ends after 90 seconds have passed or after 100 enemies have been killed, whichever comes first.
4. Only one Modifier can be used for the stage.

420124.desc:
1. In a training challenge, you can select different conditions to increase the difficulty of the training, which will also increase the number of points that can be earned upon completion.
2. Every enemy in a training challenge has a weakness. Adjusting the team lineup accordingly can make the battle easier.
3. You will receive a first completion reward upon the first completion of the training.
4. For each training challenge, only the highest points will be recorded and you will be rewarded based on the accumulated points of all training challenges.

430006.desc:
1. On Indecision and Inversion difficulties, any Modifiers or Test Modifiers can be used. However, on Disorder difficulty, only Test Modifiers can be used.
2. The challenge is time-limited. Each challenge lasts for one week, and refreshes every Monday.
3. There will be a one-week cooldown after each challenge season ends, during which the challenges will not be available.
4. Your challenge score is calculated based on the stage clear time and how many times you received attacks. Only scores from completing stages on Disorder difficulty will be entered into the rankings.
5. If you complete a stage after the challenge season has ended, your record for that stage will not be entered into the rankings. Make sure you pay attention to the challenge end time.
6. The Ranking Rewards will be issued on the Monday of the cooldown period.
7. When a challenge season ends, the rankings will be temporarily hidden until the final scores have been calculated.
8. The Ranking Rewards and Regular Rewards will be refreshed at the same time as the challenges.

440209.desc:
Dear Admin,
Hmm... I guess I should write a message of good luck, as is tradition in Xu Heng. I wish you health, wealth, and happiness, and that I can always remain by your side!

440210.desc:
Admin,
Lots of bad things can happen when the weather's cold... So... I made you these, as I was told they'll bring you luck. I don't know if they'll be useful or not, but if they can bring you some warmth... Enjoy the break. I'll be here for you in the new year.
(In the envelope are paper butterflies and exquisite sketches.)

440211.desc:
Admin,
I know we haven't known each other very long, but I feel so relaxed whenever I'm with you. I tried writing lots of different messages but I wasn't happy with any of them, so that's why this is coming to you slightly late. Anyway, I hope everything goes well for you in the new year. And...
Let's celebrate the New Year's Awakening together next year!

440212.desc:
Admin,
Wow, where has the past year gone?! I know we didn't get to spend too much time together, but I'll cherish the moments we did have.
And don't worry, I'll always be here for you.

440213.desc:
Admin,
Happy new year! It is tradition in Xu Heng to wish for wealth on this day, so may this year be one of prosperity for you. Oh yeah, I've heard that the boss did tons of fun stuff at Banchuan River this year. Would you fancy talking a walk with me there sometime?

440214.desc:
Admin,
All of a sudden, it's a new year again. Everything that happened in the old year, good or bad, is now frozen in the past. Let it all go. In this new year, may all your wishes come true, and may you carry on down your chosen path.
P.S. The new year's fireworks show is just around the corner, and I saved two tickets for it. If you have time, would you like to join me?

440215.desc:
Admin,
Happy new year! It feels like I haven't seen you in forever! Is it because I haven't been in touch, so you've forgotten all about me? Even those kids we helped once remembered to wish me happy new year before you did, but I've heard that you've been very busy, so I'll forgive you. The children miss you a lot. Will you be able to come and visit us soon?

5. Test results can be reset for you to start a new round of testing. Doing so will not affect your current mission progress.

3. Answer the questions by moving the Mod into the area with the correct answer.
4. Each round contains 15 questions, and each correct answer gains you points. Try to give correct answers in a row to gain bonus points, but be careful—you will be punished for wrong answers!

442101.desc:
1. Choose your favorite character and take part in a single-player or multiplayer game.
2. Single-player challenges have three modes. Only one of these modes will be available to play every week, with the corresponding Advanced Stages becoming available the following day.
3. Meet the requirements of the event to unlock Paw Gloves. Equip these to gain special powers.
4. In single-player challenges, players can complete three missions per week to gain an Animated Emoji Selection Pack. You can gain up to 4 of these packs in total.
5. Multiplayer games have two modes.
6. Players can get rewards based on how many times they participate and how many times they win.
7. Players can see their ranking on the event's leaderboard.

442102.desc:
1. Roll snowballs to crush snowmen within the time limit.
2. Each stage has a time limit of 120s.
3. Defeat snowmen to earn points.
4. Big Snowmen will appear at random in the field. Defeat them to gain bonus points and helpful items.
5. Items include Inflating Snowballs, Splitting Snowballs, and Hamster Snowballs. Use them at the right time to defeat more snowmen.

442103.desc:
1. Use different types of snowballs and items you pick up to defeat the snowmen.
2. The longer you charge a snowball, the further you can roll it.
3. You have a limited number of snowballs. Defeat as many snowmen as possible before you run out to get more points.
4. Extra points are given for any snowballs remaining after all snowmen have been taken out.

1. Blocks will appear on the right side of the screen. Drag them to the board and fill a row or column to clear it and earn points. The more blocks you clear, the higher your score.
2. You can also use skills, which will gradually be unlocked as you make it through more rounds.
3. Use your skills judiciously in the Limited-Time Integration Test to get more points.

477001.desc:
1. Obtain Survey Data and Research Results by performing deductions or completing survey targets.
2. Survey Data will automatically fill up the Survey Progress bar. You'll get rewards upon obtaining certain progress levels.
3. Survey Results can be used to unlock different effects in Special Research, which can assist with deductions.
4. The Research Dossier contains information on various unique items and stories. Collect enough content to earn rewards.
5. False Deduction is a challenge game mode that will be continuously updated. Survey Subjects, Survey Progress, and other in-game content will be updated in future versions.

479003.desc:
"As the Guardian of Gharpur, the Gharpur Museum asked Kali to find and bring back a stolen artifact, but things aren't always that simple..."
As a new actor in the business, we look forward to Kali's latest performance!

479007.desc:
1. You will gain Buzz each time you draw an Indicia, up to 100.
2. When Buzz is at max, the next draw will be a guaranteed Treasure Effect.

479010.desc: A large group of enemies is approaching!

479012.desc:
1. The Treasure Hunters events include Treasure Grab, Hunter's Snipe, and Boxing Arena.
2. Take part in the Treasure Grab and Hunter's Snipe stages to obtain Treasure Tablet Clues and Boxing Arena Tickets.
3. Take part in the Boxing Arena stages to obtain Treasure Tablet Clues.
4. During the Boxing Arena event, you can draw bonus Indicia to obtain stat boosts via Boxing Arena Tickets. These effects will last until the following day.
5. Treasure Tablet Clues can be exchanged for items in the Black Market Shop.

479013.desc:
1. In Treasure Grab, use skills to pull Treasure Chests into your area and achieve victory.
2. Using the same skills as the enemy will produce other incredible effects.
3. Take care when using skills. Using the wrong ones will make victory harder.
4. Appropriate use of skills will make it easier to achieve victory.
5. Treasure Chests that you have grabbed will produce treasure at regular intervals. Collecting that treasure provides Energy.

480001.desc:
1. In the Prosthetics Search event, help CORG investigate various Sephirah Zones, increase Investigation Progress, and claim Investigation Rewards.
2. During the event, 1 Sephirah Zone will open for investigation each day. Each zone will have different area effects, so choose suitable Modifiers for the investigation based on these effects.
3. Every Sephirah Zone includes Low-danger Zones and High-danger Zones. Enemies in High-danger Zones are stronger, but provide more Investigation Progress. Make sure to carry out investigation missions in the zones that suit you.
4. Obtain Countermeasure Research Points by taking part in On the Trail I and II. These points can be used in Cargo Recovery for Countermeasure Research, increasing Modifiers' combat ability and making investigation easier to complete.
5. Modifiers that successfully challenge local stages will be locked, meaning they can no longer attempt other stages in the same area. Use the reset function to reset either individual stages or entire areas. You can choose Modifiers to re-attempt challenges after the reset.

480003.desc: CORG recently uncovered a batch of illegally manufactured prosthetics flowing from Shashvat to various Sephirah Zones. Aether Gazer is currently helping CORG to track down this contraband.

482005.desc: Three contestants are needed for registration.

482010.desc:
1. The contest includes 2 phases. Each phase has different stages.
2. You can register for the competition right up until the registration deadline.
3. Players will be sorted into groups based on the number of participants after the registration deadline.
4. The winner will be decided at the corresponding time on the schedule. The results of each game can be viewed at any time.
5. During the event, daily missions will reset each day at 05:00 (UTC+0). Challenge missions can only be completed once.
6. Once the contest starts, Modifier training will not affect the competition in progress.

482011.desc:
1. To complete registration, you have to select Modifiers to take part in each competition.
2. The Modifiers used at registration will be set as Idol Competition Modifiers. They will share the same stats as the base Modifiers.
3. You can swap out and train Modifiers all the way up to the registration deadline.
4. After the registration deadline, Modifiers cannot be swapped out.
5. Training can still be done right up to the registration deadline, but training during the competition will be fixed at the value when the deadline arrives.

484001.desc: Following the intervention of the big companies uptown, the gang war in Gharpur is getting worse. In the absence of both Kali and Kubera, the reluctant Parvati has been urgently called to the field to mediate the conflict, but the gangs seem to be getting some "firepower support" from parts unknown...

484002.desc:
1. You can choose 1 of the available trial characters to participate in the game mode. Dodge incoming fire and eliminate threats!
2. Points will gradually decrease over time. Survive the barrage and eliminate the enemies as quickly as possible.
3. Carefully dodge the barrage to enter Zero Time. In Zero Time, the speed of both the barrage and enemies' movements will be reduced. Triggering Zero Time during a challenge stage will also add additional mechanics. Make skilled use of stage mechanics to eliminate Expert enemies.
4. There are five Normal Stages and three Challenge Stages in this game mode. Unlock the three Challenge stages through the Normal Stages to attempt them.

484101.desc: The Olympia Express has been commissioned by CORG to collect Bane Energy specimens and transport them to the designated location. As CORG's research partner, Aether Gazer has sent Modifiers to support and ensure the specimens are transported safely.

485001.desc:
1. Rewards are unlocked depending on how many times you've signed in, and can then be claimed.
2. Extra sign-ins will be available in the last six days of the event. Each extra sign-in costs 100 Shifted Stars. Players can use them to claim all sign-in rewards.

485002.desc: If you want to take part in the fighting competition, you'll have to be prepared. Take these. They're yours!

487001.desc: "Guess who...? Huh? You have to guess... and don't say you don't know! Come on, it's easy! Get it right and I'll give you a prize!"

487002.desc:
1. In Who I Am, open Surprise Boxes to obtain Clue Fragments. Collect 3 identical Clue Fragments to unlock the Clue's information.
2. Collect Clue Fragments to receive an event reward. The event reward can only be obtained once.
3. Complete daily missions and challenge missions to obtain Surprise Boxes.
